				 The living Gandhi
																								This is not just another compilation on Gandhi. Gopalkrishna Gandhi, the youngest son of Mohandas Karamchand Gandhis youngest son Devadas, was two-and-a-half when Gandhiji was assassinated. So the Gandhiji he knows is through other people and writings, by his grandfather and others. But Gopalkrishna took upon himself the task of bringing out the man from the tome of his own literature. The result was Oxford India Gandhi, Essential Writings. 																								One of my aims in selecting passages from his works has been to redeem the living Gandhi from the plaster-cast image of the Mahatma, writes the West Bengal governor. 																								The essential Gandhi is sought through his speeches and articles, informal diary entries, letters and conversations that provide candid pointers to why Gandhi took certain decisions or acted in a particular way both in private and public matters, says Romila Thapar. These excerpts, Gopalkrishna says, belongs to the highest genre of confessional biography. 						 ANASUYA BASU
